    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I am so sorry you are feeling this way right now. Losing everything is an incredibly heavy burden to carry, and it makes complete sense that you feel trapped and hopeless. Please know that your feelings are valid, but you do not have to stay in this hole forever.\n\nIf you are feeling like you might hurt yourself or that there is no way out, please reach out to someone who can listen without judgment. You can call or text 988 in the US and Canada to reach the Suicide & Crisis Lifeline, or text \"HOME\" to 741741 to connect with the Crisis Text Line. There are people who care about you and want to help you find a way out of this darkness.\n\nEven though it feels like everything is gone right now, there is hope for the future. Please consider reaching out to a trusted friend, family member, or mental health professional today. You are not alone in this struggle.",
